'''物理學'''（源自{{lang-grc|φυσική（ἐπιστήμη）|physikḗ （epistḗmē）|大自然的知识}}，源自{{lang|grc|φύσις}}，转写：phýsis，直譯：大自然）<ref name="etymonline-physics">{{cite web |title=physics |website=[[Online_Etymology_Dictionary|Online Etymology Dictionary]] |url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=physics&allowed_in_frame=0|accessdate=2016-11-01 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20161224191507/http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=physics&allowed_in_frame=0 |archivedate=24 December 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="etymonline-physic">{{cite web |title=physic |website=[[Online_Etymology_Dictionary|Online Etymology Dictionary]] |url=http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=physic&allowed_in_frame=0 |accessdate=2016-11-01 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20161224173651/http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=physic&allowed_in_frame=0 |archivedate=24 December 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="LSJ">{{LSJ|fu/sis|φύσις}}, {{LSJ|fusiko/s|φυσική}}, {{LSJ|e)pisth/mh|ἐπιστήμη|ref}}</ref>是研究[[物質|物質]]、[[能量|能量]]的本質與性質的[[自然科學|自然科學]]。<ref>{{cite web
 | url =https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/physics
 | title =Physics
 | website =Oxford Living Dictionaries
 | publisher =Oxford University Press
 | access-date =2016-11-05
 | quote =The branch of science concerned with the nature and properties of matter and energy
 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20161111191326/https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/physics
 | archive-date =2016-11-11
 | dead-url =no
 }}</ref>由於物質與能量是所有科學研究的必須涉及的基本要素，所以物理學是[[自然科學|自然科學]]中最基礎的學科之一。物理學是一種[[科學實驗|實驗科學]]，物理學者從觀測與分析[[大自然|大自然]]的各種基於物質與能量的現象來找出其中的模式。這些模式稱為「物理理論」，經得起實驗檢驗的常用物理理論稱為[[物理定律|物理定律]]，直到有一天被證明是有錯誤為止（具[[可否證性|可否證性]]）。物理學是由這些定律精緻地建構而成。物理學是[[自然科學|自然科學]]中最基礎的學科之一。化學、生物學、考古學等等科學學術領域的理論都是建構於這些物理定律。<ref name=Young2004>{{citation |author=H.D. Young, R.A. Freedman |year=2004 |edition=11th |title=University Physics with Modern Physics |publisher=Addison Wesley |quote=Physics is an experimental science. Physicists observe the phenomena of nature and try to find patterns and principles that relate these phenomena. These patterns are called physical theories or, when they are very well established and of broad use, physical laws or principles.  Physics is one of the most fundamental of the sciences. Scientists of all disciplines use the ideas of physics.}}</ref>{{rp|1-2}}<ref name="Giordano2009">{{cite book|author=Nicholas Giordano|title=College Physics: Reasoning and Relationships|url=https://archive.org/details/collegephysicsre0000gior_c4r0|date=2009-02-13|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=0-534-42471-6|quote=physics: the science of matter and energy, and the interactions between them}}</ref>{{rp|2-3}}

物理學是最古老的學術之一。<ref name="Giordano2009"/>{{rp|2}}物理學、[[化學|化學]]、[[生物學|生物學]]等等原本都歸屬於[[自然哲學|自然哲學]]的範疇，直到十七世紀至十九世紀期間，才漸漸地從自然哲學中分別成長為獨立的學術領域。<ref name="Grant1996">{{cite book|author=Edward Grant|title=The Foundations of Modern Science in the Middle Ages: Their Religious, Institutional and Intellectual Contexts|date=1996-10-28|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-56762-6|quote=physics, chemistry, biology… emerged as independent disciplines from  within the matrix of natural philosophy during the seventeenth to nineteenth centuries.}}</ref>{{rp|193-194}}物理學與其它很多跨領域研究有相當的交集，如[[量子化學|量子化學]]、[[生物物理學|生物物理學]]等等。物理學的疆界並不是固定不變的，物理學裡的創始突破時常可以用來解釋這些跨領域研究的基礎機制，有時還會開啟嶄新的跨領域研究。<ref name=Young2004/>{{rp|1-2}}

通過創建新理論與發展新科技，物理學對於人類文明有極為顯著的貢獻。例如，由於[[電磁學|電磁學]]的快速發展，[[電燈|電燈]]、[[電動機|電動機]]、[[家用電器|家用電器]]等新產品纷纷涌现，人類社會的生活水平也得到大幅提升。<ref name=Young2004/>{{rp|1}}<ref name="CommitteeAstronomy2001">{{cite book|author1=Physics Survey Overview Committee|author2=Board on Physics and Astronomy|author3=Division on Engineering and Physical Sciences|coauthors=National Research Council|title=Physics in a New Era: An Overview|url=https://www.nap.edu/catalog/10118/physics-in-a-new-era-an-overview|date=2001-06-15|publisher=National Academies Press|isbn=978-0-309-17089-5|access-date=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111122844/https://www.nap.edu/catalog/10118/physics-in-a-new-era-an-overview|archive-date=2016-11-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>由於[[核子物理學|核子物理學]]日趨成熟，[[核能發電|核能發電]]已不再是藍圖構想，但其所引致的[[核安全|安全問題]]也使人們意識到地球環境、生態與人類的嬌弱渺小。

== 歷史 ==
{{Main|物理學史}}
「物理」一詞在[[英文|英文]]裏是「physics」，最先出自於[[古希臘文|古希臘文]]「{{lang|el|φύσις}}」，原意是「[[自然|自然]]」。在中文裏，「物理」最早可在戰國時期佚書《鹖冠子·王鈇篇》「願聞其人情物理所以嗇萬物與天地總與神明體正之道」中找到，「物理」在這裏指的是一切事物之道理。<ref>{{cite web
 | url =http://ctext.org/he-guan-zi/wang-fu/zh
 | title =《鹖冠子·王鈇》
 | author =鶡冠子
 | publisher =中國哲學書電子化計劃
 | access-date =10-11-2016
 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20161124161410/http://ctext.org/he-guan-zi/wang-fu/zh
 | archive-date =2016-11-24
 | dead-url =no
 }}</ref>[[三國|三國]]時期，[[楊泉|楊泉]]著有《物理論》，是最早的書名含有「物理」一詞的著作。<ref>{{cite web| url =http://sci.ncu.edu.tw/wp-content/uploads/s8.pdf| title =世說新語之八，物理探原| author =劉源俊| website =東吳大學物理學系學生網| accessdate =2016-07-27| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20160807031321/http://sci.ncu.edu.tw/wp-content/uploads/s8.pdf| archivedate =2016-08-07| deadurl =yes}}</ref>明末清初科學家[[方以智|方以智]]受到西學影響，撰寫了[[百科全書|百科全書]]式著作《[[物理小識|物理小識]]》，在這裏，「物理」的含義已演化為學術之理，包括自然科學的各門領域與人文學的部分領域。<ref>{{Cite journal|author=张道扩|title=趣说生活俗语　巧学初中物理二、三例|journal=中学物理（初中版）|year=2011|issue=29|volume=11}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal
